I have a theory about what “putting the pussy on the chainwax” denotes as 
an expression.

In epic poem The Odyssey, the sirens, a collection of beautiful and 
deceptively treacherous creatures, cause sailors to crash their ship into 
adjoining rocks by distracting them with their enchanting song.  Odysseus 
outmaneuvers the sirens by having his crew plug their ears with beeswax. 
 Meanwile, he is physically restrained with chains to the mast of his ship.

By “putting the pussy on the chainwax”, Key means that the sex was so good 
that the woman plugs her ears to the pandering of other men and restrains 
herself to his “mast”.  She becomes loyal to Key (or the speaker) as 
Odysseus was to his wife, Penelope.

Keegan-Michael Key has a master of fine arts in Theater, so he almost 
certainly studied the epic thoroughly.﻿
